This paper deals with security issues in wireless networks, specifically in the context of physical-layer group secret-key generation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves network-level communications and channel measurements, which suggests the possibility of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory) categories. The paper also discusses detection techniques, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the paper involves simulations, which could suggest the possibility of cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
